This paper deals with the problem of detecting malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms and adversarial risk analysis, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a hybrid framework, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of open source software, which is relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
